HEADWORD: Boric
<hw>Bo"ric</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or containing, boron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Boric acid</b></col>, <cd>a white crystalline substance
<chform>B(OH)3</chform>, easily obtained from its salts, and occurring
in solution in the hot lagoons of Tuscany.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boride</ent>⟦br⟧
